Shichenje failed to add the third for Leopards in the 72nd minute after shooting wide with only Rangers keeper Omondi to beat.
Leopard’s dominance continued in the game as Kimani brought in Harrison Mwendwa for the jaded Peter Thiong'o.
Posta also made two changes introducing Elijah Mwanzia and Raphael Asudi for Okare and Mbugi.
In the 84th minute, Odongo pulled one back for Posta Rangers from a thunderous shot outside the box.
A rejuvenated Posta Rangers unsuccessfully pressed for the equaliser in the dying minutes but Leopards held on for maximum points ahead of the much-anticipated Mashemeji Derby. Six suspects have been arrested, and charged with carrying unregistered medicine and importing drugs without a licence. ODM leader was protesting President Uhuru Kenyatta’s new term after months of deadly election turmoil. The Health ministry said two patients died from the novel coronavirus in the past 24 hours.